# Kiosk Design System (iFCM)

All interfaces must match the self-service kiosk visual language. Source of truth: `shared/styles.css` (tokens in `:root`) and `shared/global.css` (utilities).

## Palette (strict)

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `--color-navy` | `#1E1B4B` | Primary buttons, prices, headings |
| `--color-danger` | `#E11D48` | Cancel, destructive actions |
| `--color-bg` | `#F3F4F6` | Page background |
| `--color-text-muted` | `#6b7280` | Secondary text, labels |

Never use `#1A3B6E`, orange accent, or ad-hoc colors.

## Typography

- Font: `Montserrat` via Google Fonts
- Headings/CTAs: `font-weight: 700–800`, `letter-spacing: 0.03–0.06em`, `text-transform: uppercase` for section titles and primary buttons
- Prices: `font-weight: 800`, `color: var(--color-navy)`, `font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums`

## Components

- **Cards**: `border-radius: 16px`, `box-shadow: var(--shadow-card)`
- **Primary CTA**: navy pill (`border-radius: 9999px`), `box-shadow: var(--shadow-btn-navy)`, class `btn btn-primary btn-pill btn-press`
- **Cancel**: white + rose border (`btn-outline-danger`)
- **Tabs/switchers**: pill container, active segment = navy fill (see `.auth-tabs`, `.cat-tab`, **Period tab selector** below)
- **Footers**: sticky/fixed bottom bar with `box-shadow: var(--shadow-footer)`; on long screens add **Scroll edge hint** (below)
- **Touch feedback**: always add `btn-press` on interactive elements

## Imports

```js
import '../shared/global.css'; // includes styles.css tokens
import './style.css';
```

HTML: include Montserrat from Google Fonts (see `client-lk/index.html`).

## Layout & spacing (UI/UX)

- Interface must feel **airy, clean, modern** — avoid cramped layouts.
- **Spacing grid**: multiples of 4px/8px. Use tokens: `--space-sm` (8px), `--space-md` (16px), `--space-lg` (24px).
- **Form blocks**: inputs must never stick to buttons or neighbors. Minimum gap between form sections — **16–24px**.
- **Label → input**: `--space-sm` (8px). **Between form groups**: `--space-md` (16px). **Last input → CTA button**: `--space-md` + `--space-sm` = **24px**.
- Use flex/grid containers with explicit `gap`, not margin hacks on individual fields.
- **Touch targets**: inputs and buttons `min-height: 44–48px` on mobile.

### Form pattern

```html
<div class="auth-fields"> <!-- or .form-stack -->
  <div class="form-group">...</div>
  <button class="btn btn-primary btn-pill">Submit</button>
</div>
```

```css
.auth-fields { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-md); }
.auth-fields .btn { margin-top: var(--space-sm); } /* +8px → 24px before CTA */
.form-group { gap: var(--space-sm); }
```

**Admin entity edit forms** (right panels, drawers, modals): follow `.cursor/rules/admin-form-pattern.mdc` — stack `.admin-form-stack` (gap 20px), labels `.admin-field-label`, inputs `.admin-field-input` (h-10, w-full), channel+order via `.admin-channel-grid`. **Admin master-list cards** (left sidebar): see **Admin sidebar list card** below.

## Period tab selector (B2B segmented control)

Canonical pill switcher for **period presets** and **short mutually exclusive choices** (e.g. День / Неделя / Месяц, Сегодня / Завтра). **Source of truth:** `admin/style.css` (`.period-tabs`, `.period-tab`, `.period-tab--active`). **References:** `admin/pages/reports.js`, `admin/pages/dashboard.js`.

### When to use

- Quick date-range presets in admin filters and dashboards
- Any 2–4 option toggle where one choice is active (not multi-select)
- Pair with a filter label above (`reports-filter-label` / `period-bar-label`), never inline text beside the control

### Do not

- ❌ Invent a separate gray track (`#e2e8f0`) or custom active colors for the same pattern
- ❌ Duplicate styles under new class names (e.g. `reports-kitchen-tab`) — reuse `.period-tabs` / `.period-tab`
- ❌ Use for main app navigation or more than ~4 segments — use nav tabs instead

### Structure

```html
<div class="reports-filter-field">
  <span class="reports-filter-label">Период</span>
  <div class="period-tabs" role="tablist" aria-label="Период отчёта">
    <button type="button" class="period-tab btn-press period-tab--active" data-period="week" role="tab" aria-selected="true">Неделя</button>
    <button type="button" class="period-tab btn-press" data-period="month" role="tab" aria-selected="false">Месяц</button>
  </div>
</div>
```

- Always add `btn-press` on each segment button
- Active segment: class `period-tab--active` + `aria-selected="true"`
- Optional wrapper modifier for layout only (e.g. `reports-kitchen-day-tabs`) — **no color/size overrides**

### Visual (strict)

| Part | Classes | Tokens / values |
|------|---------|-----------------|
| Track | `.period-tabs` | `background: var(--color-surface-muted)`, `border: 1px solid var(--color-border)`, `border-radius: var(--radius-pill)`, `padding: var(--space-xs)`, `gap: var(--space-xs)`, `width: fit-content` |
| Segment (default) | `.period-tab` | `color: var(--color-text-muted)`, `font-size: var(--font-size-sm)`, `font-weight: 500`, `min-height: 32px`, `padding: 6px var(--space-md)`, pill radius |
| Segment (active) | `.period-tab--active` | `background: var(--color-navy)`, `color: #fff`, `box-shadow: var(--shadow-btn-navy)` |

Typography: **sentence case**, no uppercase on segment labels (`text-transform: none`).

### Layout with filters

- Place label **above** the track (same as other filter fields: `gap: 6px`)
- In a filter row, align control baseline with dropdown triggers (`min-height: 40px` row); the track itself stays `fit-content` height (~32px inner + padding)
- On narrow screens, track may grow to `width: 100%` via a layout modifier only

## Admin sidebar list card (B2B master list)

Unified left-column row for **Группы товаров**, **Баннеры**, **Конструктор акций** (and any new admin master–detail screen). **Source of truth:** `admin/style.css` (`.avr-row--thumb`, `.cgr-row-*`, `.admin-schedule-status`), `admin/utils/schedule-status.js`, `admin/utils/product-image.js`. **References:** `category-groups-editor.js`, `marketing-banners-editor.js`, `promo-rules-editor.js`.

### When to use

- Left sidebar in `avr-layout` master–detail editors (list + right panel)
- One row = one entity; click selects for editing on the right
- Must show **channel availability (W/K)**, **schedule status**, and **deprioritized** (hidden / expired) grouping

### Row structure (strict)

All three sections use the **same DOM skeleton** — do not invent per-page variants (`mkb-list-row-btn`, `prm-row-main`, etc.):

```html
<li class="avr-row avr-row--thumb … cgr-row--hidden?">
  <button type="button" class="avr-row-main btn-press cgr-row-main" data-action="select">
    <span class="cgr-row-left">
      <span class="avr-row-thumb"><!-- thumb --></span>
      <span class="avr-row-info">
        <span class="avr-row-name">Название</span>
        <span class="avr-row-meta">Мета · <span class="admin-schedule-status …">Активно</span></span>
      </span>
    </span>
    <span class="cgr-row-indicators">
      <!-- W + K badges -->
    </span>
  </button>
</li>
```

| Zone | Classes | Notes |
|------|---------|-------|
| Row | `avr-row avr-row--thumb` | Thumb layout; add `avr-row--active` when selected |
| Button | `avr-row-main cgr-row-main` | `min-height: 64px`, flex, `padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md)` |
| Left block | `cgr-row-left` | Thumb + text, `flex: 1`, `min-width: 0` |
| Thumb | `avr-row-thumb` → `products-thumb-wrap` | **48×48px**, dark `#1e293b`, `--radius-md` |
| Meta | `avr-row-meta` | Entity summary + ` · ` + schedule status |
| Channels | `cgr-row-indicators` | `gap: 6px`, `margin-left: auto` |

Layout wrappers: `.cgr-layout`, `.mkb-layout`, `.prm-layout` — share the same row rules.

### Thumbnail fallbacks (by entity)

| Entity | Helper | Fallback |
|--------|--------|----------|
| Группа товаров | `productThumbHtml({ name, imageUrl })` | 🍽️ |
| Баннер | `productThumbHtml({ name, imageUrl })` | 🍽️ (or real image) |
| Акция | `promoThumbHtml()` | 🎁 — **never** food plate icon |

### Channel badges (W / K)

Reuse `.cgr-channel-badge` family — **do not** add text labels like «везде», «Всегда» (green), or status dots in the row.

| Badge | Active | Inactive |
|-------|--------|----------|
| **W** | `.cgr-channel-badge--web.cgr-channel-badge--active` (green) | `.cgr-channel-badge--inactive` |
| **K** | `.cgr-channel-badge--kiosk.cgr-channel-badge--active` (navy/indigo) | `.cgr-channel-badge--inactive` |

- Active + order index (groups only): `W` + `.cgr-channel-badge-num` (e.g. W1, K4)
- Promos / banners: letter only (no order index on badges)

Logic: `visibleInWeb !== false` → W active; `visibleInKiosk === true` → K active. Use `resolveChannelMode` / `channelFlagsFromMode` from `products-data.js` (or marketing equivalents).

### Schedule status label

**Always** compute via `admin/utils/schedule-status.js` — never hardcode schedule text in list meta.

```js
import { getScheduleStatus, renderListMetaWithSchedule, scheduleStatusForGroup } from '../utils/schedule-status.js';

const status = scheduleStatusForGroup(group, rulesMap.get(group.availabilityRuleId));
// meta: renderListMetaWithSchedule('2 шт.', status)
// or: renderListMetaWithSchedule(formatPromoRuleSummary(...), status)
```

| Condition | Text | Class |
|-----------|------|-------|
| No rule / always available | Всегда | `admin-schedule-status--always` |
| Before start date | Ожидает старта | `admin-schedule-status--pending` |
| After end date | Завершено | `admin-schedule-status--expired` (+ `isExpired: true`) |
| Outside time window | Перерыв | `admin-schedule-status--break` |
| In period & matching schedule | Активно | `admin-schedule-status--active` |

Markup: `<span class="admin-schedule-status ${className}">${text}</span>` inside `avr-row-meta`, after ` · `.

Entity inputs: groups/promos → `availabilityRuleId`; banners → `scheduleId` + optional `campaignDateStart` / `campaignDateEnd`.

### List sorting & deprioritized section

1. **Active rows** — visible on web or kiosk, not expired; sort per entity (groups: channel order; banners: `sortOrder`; promos: name).
2. **Bottom section** — `isHidden` (channel = Скрыт) **or** `scheduleStatus.isExpired`; class `cgr-row--hidden` (`opacity: 0.55`, muted background).
3. **Divider** before bottom block:

```html
<li class="cgr-list-divider" aria-hidden="true">
  <span class="cgr-list-divider-text">— Скрытые группы (N) —</span>
</li>
```

Use entity-specific label: «Скрытые группы», «Скрытые баннеры», «Скрытые акции». Count = all deprioritized rows.

On visibility or schedule change that affects `isExpired` / hidden → `refreshListOrder()` / re-partition list.

### Availability in edit form (right panel)

Segmented control: **Везде · Только Веб · Только Киоск · Скрыт** via `renderChannelAvailabilityGrid()` (`admin/utils/admin-form.js`).

| Entity | Order fields (Порядок Веб / Киоск) | Active toggle |
|--------|-----------------------------------|---------------|
| Группы товаров | ✅ `showOrderFields: true` (default) | ❌ use Скрыт |
| Баннеры | ❌ | ❌ |
| Акции | ❌ `showOrderFields: false` | ❌ |

`isActive` is **derived**: `visibleInWeb || visibleInKiosk`. Do not add a separate «Активен» switch.

### Groups-only: list sort bar

«Список по: Веб / Киоск» (`cgr-list-sort-bar`) — only for **группы товаров** (reorders by `webOrder` / `kioskOrder`). Not used for banners or promos.

### Do / Don't

- ✅ Same row height, thumb size, padding across cgr / mkb / prm layouts
- ✅ `cgr-row-main` + `cgr-row-left` + `cgr-row-indicators` everywhere
- ✅ `renderListMetaWithSchedule()` for meta line
- ✅ Move expired rows to bottom divider section
- ❌ Custom row classes per editor (`mkb-list-row-btn`, smaller 36px thumbs)
- ❌ Green «Всегда» / «везде» text chips in the card body
- ❌ `prm-row-status` dots — use W/K badges only
- ❌ Duplicate schedule logic outside `schedule-status.js`

## Premium Wallet Card (ID card)

Unified digital wallet card for client LK: food card number, balance, history link, and QR on one tactile surface. **Reference:** `client-lk/pages/home.js`, `client-lk/style.css` (`.lk-id-card` … `.id-card-qr`).

### When to use

- User identity / food card / balance summary in client LK
- Any “show QR at checkout” block that must feel premium and match primary CTAs

### Structure

```html
<div class="lk-id-card">
  <div class="id-card-surface">
    <div class="id-card-pattern" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="id-card-content">
      <div class="id-card-info">
        <div class="id-card-details" role="button" tabindex="0">
          <div class="id-card-label">Карта питания:</div>
          <div class="id-card-number">BD4PSTZYSKC4</div>
          <div class="id-card-balance-row">
            <span class="id-card-balance-label">Баланс:</span>
            <span class="id-card-balance">330,00 ₽</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <button class="id-card-history-link btn-press" type="button">Смотреть историю заказов &gt;</button>
      </div>
      <button class="id-card-qr btn-press" type="button" aria-label="Показать QR-код">
        <img src="…" alt="QR-код" />
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Surface & color (strict)

- **Background:** rich navy gradient — same family as `btn-primary`, never gray or violet/purple tints
  - `#35317f → #28256a → var(--color-navy) → var(--color-primary-dark)`
- **Gloss:** `::before` white sheen + navy radial highlights; `::after` subtle corner bloom — all `rgba(30, 27, 75, …)` or navy-tinted
- **Shadow:** layered floating shadow `rgba(30, 27, 75, 0.18–0.52)` — stronger than `--shadow-card`
- **Pattern:** `.id-card-pattern` — white SVG food icons, `opacity: 0.07`, `background-size: 120px`
- **Shape:** `border-radius: 20px`, `padding: 20px 20px`, `overflow: hidden`

### Typography (on card)

| Element | Size | Weight | Color |
|---------|------|--------|-------|
| Label («Карта питания:») | `--font-size-xs` | 400 | `rgba(255,255,255,0.72)` |
| Card number | `--font-size-sm` | 400 | `#fff`, `letter-spacing: 0.02em` |
| «Баланс:» | `--font-size-xs` | 400 | `rgba(255,255,255,0.72)` |
| Amount | `--font-size-xs` | 600 | `#fff`, tabular-nums |
| History link | `--font-size-sm` | 500 | `rgba(255,255,255,0.62)` → `#fff` on hover |

No balance pill/bubble — amount is plain text on the card surface.

### QR chip

- White container on the right: `80×80px`, `border-radius: 14px`, `padding: 8px` (keep ~10% padding ratio vs original `92×8`)
- `box-shadow: 0 6px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.18)` + subtle navy inset border
- Flex row: `.id-card-content` with `gap: var(--space-lg)`, `align-items: center`

### Do / Don't

- ✅ Reuse existing class names; copy styles from `client-lk/style.css`
- ✅ Keep history link inline under balance, not a separate gray block
- ❌ Gray or slate backgrounds on the card surface
- ❌ Purple/violet accent colors (`#5b4fd6`, indigo-500, etc.) — stay in navy token family
- ❌ Large bold card number — keep compact and light (400 weight)

## Scroll edge hint (fixed footer + long content)

Screens with a **fixed bottom bar** and scrollable body must show a soft shadow at the content/footer boundary when content overflows. **References:** `client-lk/utils/scroll-fade.js`, `client-lk/pages/home.js`, `client-lk/pages/payment.js`, `admin/components/layout.js`.

### When to use

- Client LK / kiosk pages: header + scrollable main + fixed CTA footer (оплата, меню, формы)
- Any time the user can scroll while a bottom action bar stays pinned

### Shell layout (required)

The scroll container must be **inside** a height-locked shell — never let `body`/`#app` scroll instead of `main`:

```css
.shell:has(.shell-footer) {
  height: 100dvh;
  max-height: 100dvh;
  overflow: hidden;
}
.shell-main {
  flex: 1;
  min-height: 0;          /* critical for flex scroll */
  overflow-y: auto;
  -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
  padding-bottom: /* footer height + safe-area */;
}
```

### Structure

```html
<div class="shell shell--pay">
  <header>…</header>
  <main class="shell-main" id="shell-main">…</main>
  <div class="scroll-fade" id="scroll-fade" hidden aria-hidden="true"></div>
  <footer class="shell-footer">…</footer>
</div>
```

### Visual (two layers)

1. **Footer shadow** — when `scrollHeight > clientHeight`: stronger upward shadow on the fixed footer (replaces subtle `--shadow-footer`):
   - `0 -10px 32px -4px rgba(30, 27, 75, 0.16), 0 -2px 8px rgba(30, 27, 75, 0.08)`
2. **Scroll fade** — when overflow **and** user has **not** reached the bottom: gradient above footer:
   - `height: 56px`, `background: linear-gradient(to bottom, transparent 0%, var(--color-bg) 80%)`
   - `position: fixed`, `bottom: {footer.offsetHeight}px`, `z-index: 19` (footer `z-index: 20`)
   - `pointer-events: none`

### JS toggle

Use `bindScrollFade()` from `client-lk/utils/scroll-fade.js`:

```js
import { bindScrollFade } from '../utils/scroll-fade.js';

this._scrollFadeCleanup = bindScrollFade({
  shell: document.querySelector('.lk-shell'),
  main: document.getElementById('lk-main'),
  fade: document.getElementById('lk-scroll-fade'),
  footer: document.querySelector('.lk-bottom-bar'),
  classScrollHint: 'lk-shell--scroll-hint',
  classHasOverflow: 'lk-shell--has-overflow',
});
```

Logic inside util:

```js
const hasOverflow = main.scrollHeight > main.clientHeight + 8;
const atBottom = main.scrollTop + main.clientHeight >= main.scrollHeight - 12;
shell.classList.toggle('shell--has-overflow', hasOverflow);
shell.classList.toggle('shell--scroll-hint', hasOverflow && !atBottom);
fade.hidden = !(hasOverflow && !atBottom);
fade.style.bottom = `${footer.offsetHeight}px`;
```

Re-bind on page render; util watches `scroll`, `resize`, `ResizeObserver`, and `MutationObserver` on `main`. Call returned cleanup on `destroy()`.

### Do / Don't

- ✅ Lock shell to `100dvh`; scroll only `.shell-main`
- ✅ Measure footer height dynamically (safe-area changes height)
- ✅ Hide fade at scroll bottom; keep footer shadow while overflow exists
- ❌ Rely on page/body scroll — fade logic will never fire
- ❌ Hard-code fade `bottom` in px without measuring footer
